From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: JohnOS <noreply@example.com>
Date: Thu, 26 Mar 2026 20:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] rock5c: recognize v4l2request for drm prime codec support

Rock 5C uses FFmpeg's V4L2 Request API decode path, which exposes hardware
decode capability via AV_HWDEVICE_TYPE_V4L2REQUEST rather than the plain DRM
device type. Teach Kodi's DRM PRIME codec registration to accept that device
type so non-GBM frontends can still discover and use the hardware decoder.
---
 xbmc/cores/VideoPlayer/DVDCodecs/Video/DVDVideoCodecDRMPRIME.cpp | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/xbmc/cores/VideoPlayer/DVDCodecs/Video/DVDVideoCodecDRMPRIME.cpp b/xbmc/cores/VideoPlayer/DVDCodecs/Video/DVDVideoCodecDRMPRIME.cpp
--- a/xbmc/cores/VideoPlayer/DVDCodecs/Video/DVDVideoCodecDRMPRIME.cpp
+++ b/xbmc/cores/VideoPlayer/DVDCodecs/Video/DVDVideoCodecDRMPRIME.cpp
@@ -77,7 +77,7 @@
   AVHWDeviceType type = AV_HWDEVICE_TYPE_NONE;
   while ((type = av_hwdevice_iterate_types(type)) != AV_HWDEVICE_TYPE_NONE)
   {
-    if (type == AV_HWDEVICE_TYPE_DRM)
+    if (type == AV_HWDEVICE_TYPE_DRM || type == AV_HWDEVICE_TYPE_V4L2REQUEST)
       return true;
   }
 
